caption: Very nice
The service was quick and the food was good. Maskw were required.
Now they are open for dining service. Food is still excellent.

This restaurant is doubtless one of the most pleasant place in the area. Always when I come to this place I am absolutely pleased. They keep their very high  level service and the highest level of cooking  they offer. You always win with this restaurant. Highly  recommended.

I get delivery from here at least twice a month, it's my go-to place for sure! Everything is delicious and piping hot every time. My favorites are the pad see ew, crispy pork kraprow, the spring rolls, and the curry puffs! So so good and not too crazy heavy either.

CUSTOMER SERVICE IS ON ZERO!!!!!! They're EXTREMELY rude and don't take accountability for mistakes. I very calmly told her my order was wrong, and she told me "you need to get out now!" I'm assuming because of Covid, you're just supposed to pick up and go. But how do you supposed to let them know they're handing me someone else's food? lol... How are you rude to the people that support you? I rarely leave reviews, but figured I should let others know you probably won't be respected much when you go in there.
Delectable Thai food at a great price. Their curry puff and chive pancakes are must for apps. Make sure to order through their website - easy and quick delivery.

WORST fried calamari I have ever tasted, not fresh & rubbery! I’m disgusted also got a pad Thai w peanut sauce and the peanut sauce tasted sour. Think I have peanut sauce at home maybe I can mix it in :(

I walk by this place all the time and decided to give it a shot and it did not disappoint! We were very impressed with the appetizers and their sauces (curry puffs and chicken satay) and loved the curry and the noodles we ordered as well. This will be our new go to spot!  Looking forward to trying some of the duck dishes.
Had so much hope for the chicken over rice, thought it would just be like the Khao mon gai, turns out to be broiled chicken breast over rice. Plain. Extremely disappointed.
Great food and the staff are courteous
This food is disgusting and greasy
Very neat and accessible spot. They serve big meals and for affordable prices. I liked the meals a lot and the staff members were very friendly and chatty. Will definitely recommend this place.
Delicious food and fast delivery during this lockdown. Thank you!

Horrible customer service. Placed 2 orders on Grubhub, but only received one. Called to get information and got the worst service. Was placed on hold, then someone came back and just said "call back" and hung up. I couldnt believe it. I don't care how good the food might be, they will never get my business again!
For Thai food in Brooklyn they are good.

I had a date w my boyfriend at Holic Thai but there were closed due to a electric problem. So we decided to come here. At first we were hesitant since we have been going to the Holic place for over 3 years. But I gotta say, the food is amazing! It’s delicious and affordable. Plus is Bring your own bottle ! We love it !
Pretty good Thai cooking. We had a carry out order. Pad Thai was great but not excellent like some restaurants in Bangkok, in all fairness, they are pretty good
Really like their ground chicken basil with fried egg - just got the right amount of basil and spicy kick. Nice and comfortable interior round this place out!
Average thai food. Average menu with lunch special.
Great for eating in or taking out. Your typical Thai but always hot, fresh and delicious. Have never been let down by their food.
It was nice. We had the lunch special... Only thing is the appetizer was only one Puff I think it should have at least been three. Lovely scenery nice music definitely worth it.

All right, I was looking for something different, good and classic! Then I found this place and even better, they have like a lunch special!! Were two appetizers and a delicious main plate! For 8,50$ + tax!! it’s a really good plate! I tried pork fried rice (classic) and was really good! Tasty and lovely!! Coconut water was a really good choice to combine.. Restaurant is cozy and servers make me feel comfortable.. for sure I’ll be back..

Good food. But never on time for their delivery. They say it will take an one hour, but 1.5 hours later it is still not delivered. Luckily there are other Thai places that are more prompt with their delivery. Not worth the wait!

I Absolutely love this place.. the staff, decor & the beautifully display of fresh delicious thai cuisine is priceless!!  I've had lunch on several occasions with my parents here.  Some how my review was mixed up with another establishment..  I want all the praise to go where it belongs!  ACE Thai Kitchen
Food is absolutely delicious! We had the duck, mixed seafood and spicy chicken,  will definitely be back on our next visit to NYC
Quincy...always polite and helpful. Food was also great!
The food was very affordable and good

I enjoyed my total experience there. We were the last customers tonight but we were welcome with excellent service and food. We ordered Tom Yum soup and it was yummy and packed with vegetables. We also ordered salmon pad kraprow and the salmon was cooked perfectly and the dish was sooo flavorful. The food was so good that we ordered food for tomorrow. We will definitely be back soon.

Ace Thai Kitchen has a lovely ambiance very intimate.  The food is absolutely delicious.  My son loves the Ace Wings.  I love the Calamari cooked perfectly.   I just ate a combination of broccoli and bok choy.  The garlic sauce is so yummy.  Definitely have to mention the Thai Tea.  The customer service is welcoming.  Thank you.  I highly recommend this spot😍
Great clean restaurant with a great environment plus awesome service and Delicious food!!! 100% recommended to everyone!!!
Visiting Brooklyn and I've been eating here few times. Fresh, tasty and friendly every time! My favorite Thai spot in the hood
Some Dam good Thai food in NYC
(Translated by Google) Nice service, delicious food, clean. Perfect. Thank you for the lovely evening.  (Original) Nette Bedienung, sehr leckeres Essen, sauber. Perfekt. Danke für den schönen Abend.
Love the food
Nice place to eat some good taï food in Brooklin
Excellent food and service….. My second time here and they have the best thai food ihave ever tasted…. Waitress was helpful and friendly

This place is a good addition to the neighborhood. It’s not so crowded, and you can find a table right away. For those who don’t love cilantro and super spicy food, this is the place to go! In general, food is good and well presented. The staff is friendly and the atmosphere is relaxed.
Had amazing curry tonight and the customer service was awesome.
Great service and absolutely amazing Thai food!! Highly recommend
Love the food but sometimes it's a hit or miss. Price is decent and the staff is very friendly.
Staff is friendly Foods are amazing A place is cozy. It's great to have a dinner with friends or family.
Staff and food were perfect
Exceptional food and service - wholly deserving of your patronage. Get here!

Came here yesterday in hopes of trying out this Thai restaurant. I was seated, and put in my appetizer order right away. Sat there and drank all my water. Looked around maybe only 3 tables filled. 20 minutes goes by, no body comes to refill our water or takes our main entree order. I get up to see what the hold up was and the waiter was literally just standing there. As we got up to leave, he apologized and said he was the only waiter working. Although he was very nice about it, there were only 3 tables filled in the entire restaurant, And he wasn’t even busy. he could’ve came to see if we needed more water or came to take our main entree order in the meantime. I lived in Thailand for years, so I was excited to try this place and never would walk out of a restaurant unless the service was that bad... and it was that bad. Went to thaiholic instead and got our food 5 minutes after we sat down.

My husband n I have visited Ace Thai Kitchen twice n both times were really nice experiences. The service and staff were awesome. The food is very good n flavorful. They always have really good music playing. Love the decor. A little to dim for my mature eye's but very nice atmosphere.
Beautiful atmosphere and great food. Place is very inviting and hospitable.
My new favorite Thai on myrtle ave!!
Very nice

It's the newest in the neighborhood- everything I ordered well portioned and flavors not overbearing nor salty. I must come back in 6 months to see if their presentation + flavor + quality maintains - then maybe a 5. Spacious for a company event + clean + attentive... will recommend. Price reasonable.
Yummy
Found this little place visiting Brooklyn.  Great lunch prices, all the food was amazing, from soup, to spring rolls, to the chicken pad thai I ordered. Next time I'm in town would definitely visit.

Excellent food and affordable lunch menu. This was only my first time; I had the pad Thai and it was one of the best pad Thais I have ever had. I am so thankful this is a new spot in the neighborhood.

Here now with my family cant get enough of this place definately coming back ,as u came in every body greeted you the guy serve the food was awsome ...tasty delicious food awsome clean place ...love it..
Wonderful place and very friendly staff.

Best thai food on myrtle ave! so happy this place opened compared to the other 3 thai restaurants. Their prices are reasonable for the portion of food. Plus their customer service is friendly. My only issue is that they don't have large size thai ice teas.
Great food, great service. I’ve been looking for quality Thai food in the area for a long time now, and Ace Thai finally satisfied my needs.
I think their food really taste good

This place rules! My boyfriend said the food was as good as in Thailand - I watched him eat spicy Thai basil chicken and he was in heaven. See the after shot. I'm a vegetarian and I had the eggplant appetizer where they slice it down the middle and roast it, add a spicy sweet sauce. Ate the whole 'plant even the top which was very flavorful. Tofu and vegetable soup was delicious, the bowl was the size of my head and a half - devoured it. Staff was friendly and perfectly attentive. Too full for dessert but it looked tasty - will be going back.

Came here for lunch since its new i was willing to try it out. The place is nice the staff were very friendly. The food i really enjoyed because the lunch is a great deal which i highly recommend. Also it is enough for 1 person. The lunch special is worthwhile. I ordered the chicken pineapple fried rice with the soup and as an appetizer i got the curry puff and the gyoza. Now i will say that i enjoyed the soup because it was actually spicy and im a lover of spicy food. The appetizers were also very delicious. Over all i would recommend ppl to eat her and I will be returning.
Really good Thai! So glad this place has opened in the neighborhood!!
I went there twice. Great service. They make the best krapow crispy pork.

Best Pad Seew ever! Tastes exactly like the one I had when I was visiting Thailand before. Noodle texture is unique and sauce is full of flavor! My new go to Thai place 😊 Service was excellent, looking forward to trying the other dishes.

When I went to pick up the order I placed by phone I noticed I was charged $2 extra for my soup. I questioned this and was told by the woman helping me I was charged extra because I ordered shrimp and chicken in my soup. I told her I only ordered shrimp. Then she told me shrimp was extra. I opened the menu to show her this wasn’t the case.  She told me the menu was wrong!  We argued this point, until I told her to just remove the soup from my bill. Unfortunately she’d already charged my card & didn’t know how to void the charge.  Finally about 10 minutes later the charges were resolved and I left the restaurant with my food which was now colder than it was warm, under my arm.  As I turned the corner off of Myrtle a woman from the kitchen ran after me offering soup gratis, with many apologies.  It was a very kind gesture.  I would ignore all of this trouble if the food was good, however that was not the case. The vegetarian main course I ordered with string beans and peppers had a scant few of both. I was looking forward to having a new Thai restaurant close to home, but I am sorry to say I won’t be returning.

I'm bummed that I'm about to move out of the neighborhood. If I was staying any longer this place would be my new go to Thai spot. Since they opened a week ago I've eaten in with my girlfriend, and ordered take out for myself. The food is surprisingly good. I've had the Panang Curry, Pad Thai, and Ba Mee Pooh Moo Dang which were all great, and the Curry Puffs were super tasty.  It's a great spot, and the service is excellent. I'm happy to see a restaurant like this move into the neighborhood even though I'm moving out.
